resources.string: Xiaomi Corporation (/ˈʃaʊmiː/;[2] Chinese: 小米 [ɕjǎu.mì] (About this soundlisten)) is a Chinese electronics company headquartered in Beijing. Xiaomi makes and invests in smartphones, mobile apps, laptops, and related consumer electronics.[3]

Samsung (Hangul: 삼성; Hanja: 三星; Korean pronunciation: [samsʌŋ]; means "tristar" in English) is a South Korean multinational conglomerate headquartered in Samsung Town, Seoul.[1] It comprises numerous affiliated businesses, [1] most of them united under the Samsung brand, and is the largest South Korean chaebol (business conglomerate).

iPhone (/ˈaɪfoʊn/ EYE-fone) is a line of smartphones designedand marketed by Apple Inc. All generations of the iPhone use Apple.s iOS mobile operating system software. The first-generation iPhone was released on June 29, 2007,and multiple new hardware iterations with new iOS releases have been released since.

Huawei Technologies Co. Ltd. (/ˈhwɑːˌweɪ/; simplified Chinese: 华为; traditional Chinese: 華為; pinyin: About this soundHuáwéi) is a Chinese multinational telecommunications equipment and consumer electronics manufacturer, headquartered in Shenzhen, China.

Nokia Corporation (commonly referred to as Nokia; UK: /ˈnɒkiə/, US: /ˈnoʊkiə/, Finnish: [ˈnokiɑ]) is a Finnish multinational telecommunications, information technology, and consumer electronics company, founded in 1865. Nokia.s headquarters are in Espoo, in the greater Helsinki metropolitan area.
